2026-05-23 | Convert Binary Tree to Sum Tree

	Question
Convert tree into Sum Tree.
	Key Insight
We need subtree sums before updating parent.  
So:
		process children first
		then update current node.
This is exactly:
		Postorder Traversal
		(left → right → node)
	Approach
1.	Recursively compute:
		left subtree sum
		right subtree sum
2.	Store original node value  
3.	Update current node:
		node->data = leftSum + rightSum
4.	Return:
		original value + new subtree sum
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(h)
	where h = tree height
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int solve(Node* root){
        if(root == NULL)
            return 0;
        int leftSum = solve(root->left);
        int rightSum = solve(root->right);
        int oldValue = root->data;
        root->data = leftSum + rightSum;
        return oldValue + root->data;
    }
    void toSumTree(Node *node) {
        solve(node);
    }
};
	Key Insight
Postorder traversal ensures:
		children are processed before parent  
That allows correct subtree sums
before modifying current node.
